Absolute value is 4. Alternatively, maybe there is a mistake in the sign during shoelace. Let me check the shoelace formula again. The shoelace formula is 1/2 |sum(x_i y_{i+1} - x_{i+1} y_i)|. The order of the points is crucial. If the points are not ordered correctly (either clockwise or counter-clockwise), the result can be wrong. Let me verify the order of the points. Looking at the coordinates: 1. (0,1 - sqrt(3)) -- left, bottom 2. (1,1 - sqrt(3)) -- right, bottom 3. (3 - sqrt(3), sqrt(3) - 2) -- right, bottom-left 4. (sqrt(3), 0) -- center right, bottom 5.
